<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
At first I loved the idea... the graphics on the "character homepage" are beautiful and the idea that it could be done automatically extremely appealing (even though I do get most of my enjoyment out of "tracking" my characters instead of playing them and have generated many Word docs and Excel spreadsheets to transfer info from in-game to web sites without Alt-Tab).<P>Then I thought about it a bit... $40 a month is a lot of money... and it's only 8 characters... I have 18 characters and don't want to start new ones just for Legends, and the ones I'd most want to have Legends homepages for are guilded and not moving.<P>I'd be willing to pay $5 or $10 extra for the web pages (maps, homepage, events, guild tracking) on my normal server (for as many characters as I create, not limited to 8)... but I won't be joining Legends as it currently is.<P>And I agree about the events, items, and CS... doesn't bode well for the "live" servers.    <IMG SRC="http://www.eqatlas.com/ubb/frown.gif"><p>[This message has been edited by Evenstar (edited 02-09-2002).]
