<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I agree with you completely Muse and I share with you my further thoughts on the subject. <BR>My first prediction: they will not get 8000 sign ups but they will get 2000, they will consider that not enough to continue the venture, thus having 2000 extremely disgruntled customers. Worse PR.<BR>Should that prediction not come to light, my second predicted scenario is this: a few groups of well seasoned veterans will go over to Legends for 3 months max, try to loot everything new and of value, then transfer back expecting to make a small fortune in game. Even more bad PR and bad interrelations between gamers within the so-called “economy” of the game. Which I think is horrible anyway and should depend more on trade skills.<BR>I started playing the game about 18 months ago and put it away when I was about 6 or 7 levels into it finding little interest in the social demands of grouping with 14-year-old boys. <BR>I picked the game back up in September of last year when both my children wanted to play with me and we have had a very good time doing this as a family. However, this means that I am already paying for 3 separate accounts, I have three machines which have all been upgraded to 512 ram and gforce 3 cards, not to mention the cost of the software itself for each account. <BR>This brings me to my even more personal issue on PR.<BR>I attended the Fan Faire in Dallas, not only coming early but paying for and bringing my daughter i.e.: hotel expenses, meals, and entry fees. We were both never so disappointed in all our lives. <BR>The only saving grace of the whole affair was meeting Keith Parkinson, purchasing several prints from him, and having him personally sign them. He is a very nice gentleman indeed.  <BR>Since I purchased my software so long ago, I have EQ and Kunark but at the time Velious did not exist. It seems to be only available now by purchasing the trilogy pack. <P>I personally asked Gordon in the bar of the hotel where I could get the expansion pack without having to buy even more software I already owned. I have already purchased two of the trilogy packs, three SOL expansions and the original EQ/kunark set. His response to me was that I would have to talk to someone in marketing. He did not so much as offer me a name, a phone number, or anything else to help me.  At that point, my respect for the staff wavered immensely and I realized that we, the gamers were not looked upon as real people, not even viewed as important clients, we were but sheep following the wolf to the cave. I am not alone in this thought, I have other professional friends that play and we have begun to compare notes, especially after the fan faire. They may continue to dupe the younger players out of their allowance money, but if they continue with PR the way it’s going, they will certainly loose those of us with the bankrolls to support them.
</FONT>
